douglas m baker jr  wikipedia douglas m baker jr from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search douglas m baker jr born december   is chairman of the board and chief executive officer of ecolab inc a fortune  company in water hygiene and energy technologies and services contents  career  community involvement  education  references careeredit baker joined ecolab in  initially holding various marketing and leadership positions in the us and europe including vice president and general manager of kay chemical co a division of ecolab that provides cleaning and sanitizing programs tailored specifically for the quick food service fast food and food retail supermarket and grocery markets later baker became junior vice president of ecolab’s institutional business sector which provides cleaning and sanitation products programs and services to food service hospitality healthcare and commercial customers in north america baker was named ecolab’s president and chief operating officer in  president and chief executive officer in  and added chairman of the board responsibilities in  through  ecolab sales had grown  percent to  billion and adjusted eps had increased  percent to  per share during his tenure as ceo baker has received numerous awards and recognition throughout his career most recently he was named to the forbes global  hall of fame ceos and named  responsible ceo of the year by corporate responsibility magazine before joining ecolab baker spent seven years with procter  gamble in various brand management positions in addition to his ecolab responsibilities baker serves as a member of the board of directors of us bancorp and target corporation he also is trustee emeritus of the national restaurant association educational foundation community involvementedit baker is active in the civic life of the twin cities of minneapolis and st paul minn he serves on the executive committee of the greater msp partnership a privatepublic partnership whose mission is to stimulate economic growth and prosperity in the region baker also serves on the board of overseers of the carlson school of management at the university of minnesota and on the executive committee of the minnesota business partnership an organization of ceos from minnesota’s top  companies focused on further enhancing the region’s quality of life he is a board member of parent aware for school readiness pasr a nonprofit organization to support the statewide expansion of parent aware minnesota’s quality rating and improvement system baker and his wife julie also chaired the  twin cities united way fundraising campaigncitation needed baker also is a cochair of the host committee for super bowl lii which will be held in february  in minneapolis  educationedit baker earned a bachelor of arts degree from college of the holy cross in worcester mass where he majored in english he currently serves on the colleges board of trustees referencesedit  ecolab ceo bakers pay rises to m exnalco ceo gets m  minneapolis  st paul business journal bizjournalscom  retrieved    ecolab new releases httpwwwecolabcommediacenternewsreleases  exec of year doug baker ecolab   forbes global  hall of fame ceos httpwwwforbescomsitessteveschaeferglobalamericantowergileadryanairnrgenergy  douglas m baker jr bio httpwwwecolabcomourstoryourleadershipmeetourchairmanandceo  archived copy archived from the original on  retrieved     retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitledouglasmbakerjroldid categories american chemical industry businesspeopleamerican technology chief executivesliving peopleprocter  gamble people birthshidden categories all articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from october  navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction