oming president and chief executive officer in july  in may  baker added chairman of the board to his duties  in addition to his ecolab responsibilities baker serves on the board of directors of target corporation and us bancorp he is trustee emeritus of the national restaurant association educational foundation a member of the committee encouraging corporate philanthropy cecp and is involved in a number of community initiatives in the minneapolisst paul area  baker received a bachelor’s degree in english from college of the holy cross in worcester mass and serves on the college’s board of trustees   theodore m hesburgh award acceptance the university of notre dame’s mendoza school of business presented ecolab with the  theodore m hesburgh award for ethical and socially responsible business practices ecolab chairman and ceo douglas m baker jr accepted the award on behalf of the company  financial times water summit presentation ecolab chairman and ceo doug baker presented the closing keynote address on how businesses can achieve growth in an era of water scarcity at the  ft water summit in london   pwc  us ceo survey during his pwc ceo survey interview doug baker gives his perspective on how technology and partnerships are crucial for the delivery of services that meet basic human needs  economic club of mn food security summit ecolab chairman and ceo doug baker participated in a panel discussion on food security at the  economic club of minnesota food security summit watch video douglas m baker jr english investors safety data sheets login search douglas m baker jr doug baker is chairman of the board and chief executive officer of ecolab inc baker began his career with ecolab in  and has held key roles in marketing sales and management in the us and europe  in july  baker was named president and chief executive officer and in may  added chairman of the board to his duties home about leadership douglas m baker jr contact us expand get in touch with unparalleled expe