isclosed “this sale enables us to sharpen our strategic focus on our core business areas while assuring vehicle care customers will receive excellent ongoing product and service support from a longestablished provider in the industry in addition our vehicle care colleagues will be part of a business in which they will be more closely aligned and have access to the tools and resources that will support growth we thank them for their many contributions and wish them every success in the future” said douglas m baker jr chairman and ceo ecolab  woc news    comments login your comments up to  characters please respect our community and the integrity of its participants woc reserves the right to moderate and approve your comment submit related news koppers forms tar distillation facility jv in china pittsburgh us koppers holdings inc has approved the formation of a majorityowned joint venture company by its whollyowned subsidiary koppers inte  read more polypropylene revenues to be  bn in  says ceresana study konstanz germany a dynamic growth of worldwide revenues for polypropylene one of the most versatile plastics is expected amounting to more than   read more new research provides insight into how the solar wind heats up warwickshire uk new research led by dr kareem osman physicist university of warwick has provided significant insight into how the solar wind heats  read more dow agrosciences and acpfg to collaborate on crop development indianapolis usadelaide australia dow agrosciences a wholly owned subsidiary of dow chemical company and the australian centre for plant function  read more some food flavours have moodenhancing effects philadelphia us new evidence reveals the possibility of moodenhancing effects associated with some flavours stemming at least in part from natural  read more comac boeing to develop biofuels from waste cooking oil beijing china commercial aircraft corp of china comac and boeing opened the boeingcomac aviation energy conservation and emis